istal dilatation of the spongy urethra is the cunicular fossa","The external urethral sphincter surrounds the membranous urethra"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe male urethra has four distinct anatomical segments:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eintramural\u003C/strong\u003E portion passes through the bladder wall and contracts (not dilates) during ejaculation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal urethral sphincter\u003C/strong\u003E is located at the bladder neck, not around the prostatic urethra\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eprostatic urethra\u003C/strong\u003E passes through the prostate gland and is not located in the deep perineal pouch\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe distal dilatation is called the navicular fossa, not the \u003Cstrong\u003Ecunicular fossa\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eexternal urethral sphincter\u003C/strong\u003E is a skeletal muscle that surrounds the membranous urethra and provides voluntary control of micturition\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The male urethra has four parts: intramural, prostatic, membranous, and spongy (penile).","The external urethral sphincter surrounds the membranous urethra and is under voluntary control.","The internal urethral sphincter surrounds the bladder neck and is under autonomic control."],"references":["Serbanoiu A, Ion RT, Filipoiu F, Tulin A, Enyedi M. Dissection of the Male Urethra Demonstrating Its Topographical Specificity. Cureus. 2024 Aug 1;16(8):e65946. doi: 10.7759/cureus.65946. PMID: 39221353; PMCID: PMC11365459","Stoddard N, Leslie SW. Histology, Male Urethra. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK542238/","Karam I, Moudouni S, Droupy S, Abd-Alsamad I, Uhl JF, Delmas V. The structure and innervation of the male urethra: histological and immunohistochemical studies with three-dimensional reconstruction. J Anat. 2005 Apr;206(4):395-403. doi: 10.1111/j.1469-7580.2005.00402.x. PMID: 15817107; PMCID: PMC1571491","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53493"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15780"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53493","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53493"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-08T17:13:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-08T17:13:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8471"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68028"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":